      • setSelectedRowIndexInScenarioTable

        public void setSelectedRowIndexInScenarioTable(int rowIndex)
        Set selection in scenario JTable. Why in this class? It is GUI stuff! Because some Actions have use this method and Actions only have access to the model. "actions only access the model" -- that seems pretty idealistic. We already break this concept by using VadereWindow's getMainWindow().
